                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14958762" author="srowen" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2015 11:39:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this specific to dynamic allocation though? you could have the same problem without it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14960169" author="rdub" created="Fri, 16 Oct 2015 04:54:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Without dynamic allocation, you are allowed &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;twice the number of executors&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; failures, which seems reasonable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With dynamic allocation, &lt;tt&gt;spark.executor.instances&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t get set, and so you are allowed &lt;tt&gt;math.max(0 * 2, 3)&lt;/tt&gt; failures, no matter how many executors your job has as its min, initial, and max settings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14960174" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 16 Oct 2015 04:58:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;ryan-williams&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/9147&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/9147&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
